other_tests.findings: Severe orbital myiasis due to Cochliomyia hominivorax infestation with significant necrosis and extensive tissue destruction.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Significant improvement in swelling and death of the larvae followed initial treatment with ivermectin; however, enucleation was required in the first patient due to advanced ocular involvement.

other_tests.findings: The larvae extracted in the first case were identified as Cochliomyia hominivorax.
Moderately differentiated squamous cell carcinoma of the skin in the first patient and ulcerated skin basocellular carcinoma in the second patient.
